data: Yui arrives in the new mysterious house and meets the six mysterious brothers who are actually vampires but none of them knew about her arrival except Shuu who explains that he received a call the other day from a man and he told him to keep her safe and not to kill her. Soon, Yui learns that she is the prospective bride and she tries to run but ends up in an abandoned room where she finds her dad's diary and discovers that she is adopted. The episode ends with Yui yelling for help as she was cornered by the six vampire brothers.

It is the first day at a new high school for Yui but she finds it strange that the high school is at night. On their way to school she notices that all the brothers are different from each other and don't seems to get along. Later at school Ayato forces himself on Yui and sucks her blood and does not stop until Reiji comes and tells him to take his activities to his private room. Later, Ayato throws Yui in the swimming pool and orders her to say that he is great but Yui can't swim and asks for help. Ayato than has a flashback of his childhood and after that he jumps in pool to save Yui. He kisses Yui underwater to wake her up and suck her blood; Yui begs him to stop and he stops, telling her he will continue later. At the end of episode Yui goes back to the abandoned room to see her dad's diary but finds it blank and is confused by this.

Yui finally finds out from Shu that the brothers are different from each other because they all have different mothers: he and Reiji have same mother, Ayato, Kanato and Laito are triplets from another mother, and Subaru has a different mother. After that Yui grabs Shuu's hand to pull him out of the bathtub and on touching her hand he has a flashback about a human boy Edgar who died in a fire. He pulls Yui into the tub and tells her that he wants to suck her blood (possibly make her hate him so she doesn't get too attached to him). Yui is shocked as she thought he was different but he tells her he is a vampire. Later that night Ayato also tries to suck Yui's blood but is displeased to find bite marks on her neck, so he challenges Shuu to a dart match for which the prize will be Yui. Shuu wins the match and is about to leave without claiming the prize but Laito pushes Yui towards him. The episode ends with Shuu telling Yui in a serious tone that to him "mortals are just prey."
